 {"id":"bd-lff4p.12.1","title":"Design: JS/WASM contract for showcase runner (inputs, resize, patches, determinism)","description":"Goal
- Define the exact API/ABI contract between:
  1) the browser host (HTML+JS),
  2) `FrankenTermWeb` (web terminal surface), and
  3) the showcase app runner compiled to WASM.

Why This Is Its Own Bead
- If we lock this down first, all downstream work (runner implementation, HTML glue, tests, CI) becomes mechanical and verifiable.

Inputs Contract
- Browser captures DOM events and feeds them to `FrankenTermWeb.input(eventObj)` to normalize them to deterministic JSON strings.
- Host drains `FrankenTermWeb.drainEncodedInputs()` and forwards each JSON string to the showcase runner.
- Runner must parse the encoded input format into `ftui_core::event::Event` (or into the app `Message`) without any browser-only dependencies.

Resize Contract
- Define what the runner consumes on resize:
  - terminal cols/rows (cell-space), OR
  - pixel size + DPR (if runner needs it), OR
  - both.
- Ensure `FrankenTermWeb.resize(cols, rows)` is invoked in lockstep with runner resize so both agree on geometry.

Patch Contract
- Runner emits patch batches compatible with `FrankenTermWeb.applyPatchBatchFlat(spans: Uint32Array, cells: Uint32Array)`.
- Specify exact invariants:
  - span format: `[offset, len, offset, len, ...]` (len measured in cells)
  - cell format: `[bg, fg, glyph, attrs, ...]` u32 words per cell
  - batch ordering, stability guarantees, and whether empty batches are allowed

Determinism / Time
- Runner must be able to run in:
  - real-time mode (requestAnimationFrame-driven), and
  - fixed-step replay mode (for golden traces + CI).
- Define how time is injected (e.g., `step(dt_ms)`), and what is recorded in logs.

Logging Contract
- Standardize JSONL log lines for:
  - input events (already stable JSON from FrankenTermWeb)
  - runner step boundaries (frame_idx, dt, view_id)
  - patch stats (spans count, cells changed, bytes)
  - optional frame hashes (to support correctness gates).

Acceptance Criteria
- A written contract (in this bead description is fine) is agreed upon and is implementable with existing crates.
- Downstream tasks can reference this contract verbatim without re-deciding formats.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-10T03:11:08.744717040Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-10T03:11:08.744717040Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["design","showcase","wasm","web"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-lff4p.12.1","depends_on_id":"bd-lff4p.12","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-10T03:11:08.744717040Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-lff4p.12.2","title":"Fix WASM build: ftui-core tracing feature must compile on wasm32","description":"Background
- The web showcase demo requires building a subset of the ftui stack for `wasm32-unknown-unknown`.
- `ftui-core` has a `tracing` feature that is used by higher layers for instrumentation.
- Current issue: enabling `ftui-core` `tracing` on `wasm32-unknown-unknown` fails to compile because the optional `tracing` dependency is placed under a unix-only target dependency section in `crates/ftui-core/Cargo.toml`.

Root Cause (Expected)
- Optional deps for the `tracing` feature must be available on wasm targets too (or the feature must be cfg-gated).
- Today the feature compiles on unix but not on wasm because the dependency is not in scope for the wasm target.

What "Done" Means
- `ftui-core` compiles on wasm when `--features tracing` is enabled, without weakening the feature model.

Repro
- `cargo check -p ftui-core --target wasm32-unknown-unknown --features tracing`

Fix Sketch
- Move `tracing` (and any required optional deps) into normal `[dependencies]` with `optional = true`, and keep platform-specific extras behind appropriate cfgs.
- Ensure `ftui-core/src/logging.rs` compiles cleanly on wasm with `tracing` enabled (may require `cfg` around subscriber setup if any).

Validation
- `cargo check -p ftui-core --target wasm32-unknown-unknown --features tracing`
- `cargo check -p ftui-web --target wasm32-unknown-unknown` (sanity)
- Follow-on: `cargo check -p ftui-demo-showcase --target wasm32-unknown-unknown` once the runner crate exists.

Notes
- This bead is a hard prerequisite for the browser showcase runner and for CI to gain a wasm check job.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-02-10T03:11:21.559356360Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-10T03:11:21.559356360Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["build","ftui-core","tracing","wasm"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-lff4p.12.2","depends_on_id":"bd-lff4p.12","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-10T03:11:21.559356360Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
